sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I724001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: LacI + ECFP under luxpR, with autoinducer inactivation
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This construct made with J40001 and I724000. LacI and ECFP are LVA tagged, and are regulated by the R0062 LuxR/HSL promoter. The autoinducer inactivation is also regulated by the R0062 LuxR/HSL promoter, and it gives a repressilator system more control.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Hanmo Li

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I724000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Autoinducer inactivation enzyme regulated by LuxR/HSL promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: We made this construct with LuxR/HSL promoter R0062, B0034 RBS, and the C0060 aiiA gene in order to give us more control with our repressilator system. The aiiA gene will be turned on by the LuxR/HSL promoter in the presence of the LuxR activator protein complexed with the autoinducer 3-oxo-hexanoyl-HSL.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Hanmo Li

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J40001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: LacI (LVA) + ECFP (LVA) under luxpR promoter (LuxR/HSL regulated)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Polycistronic LacI and ECFP proteins with degradation tags regulated by luxpR promoter (expression up-regulated by LuxR/HSL complex).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Horia Vulpe

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lux pR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Promoter activated by LuxR in concert with HSL

The lux cassette of V. fischeri contains a left and a right promoter. The right promoter gives weak constitutive expression of downstream genes.This expression is up-regulated by the action of the LuxR activator protein complexed with the autoinducer, 3-oxo-hexanoyl-HSL. Two molecules of LuxR protein form a complex with two molecules of the signalling compound homoserine lactone (HSL). This complex binds to a palindromic site on the promoter, increasing the rate of transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This promoter is based on the Vibrio fischeri quorum sensing gene promoters. Two genes LuxI and LuxR and transcribed in opposite directions as shown below. The original sequence from which the parts BBa_R0062 and BBa_R0063 were derived is shown in the picture below.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Coding region for the LacI protein with an LVA degradation tail and without an RBS. LacI binds to the pLac regulator BBa_R0010 and PLlac01 hybrid regulator BBa_R0011 and inhibits transcription. IPTG (Isopropylthiogalactoside) binds to LacI and inhibits its operation, therefore promoting transcription.

A rapid degredation tail (LVA) has been added to improve the High to Low performance of this part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
References (unparsed) here:

Elowitz, M.B., Leibler, S. A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators. Nature 403, 335-338 (2000). [ELOW00]

References (unparsed) here:

Elowitz, M.B., Leibler, S. A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators. Nature 403, 335-338 (2000). [ELOW00]

Sequence taken from the repressilator of Elowitz and Leibler (2000). The obtained sequence was compared to the wild-type sequence for LacI obtained through a database search. The sequence had been modified from the wild-type in that wild-type GTG start was changed to an ATG start (note, actual ORF in E.coli has several GTG starts it would seem). The LVA tag has been added for quicker degradation.

Incompatible with systems containing LacI, lactose, or IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Grace Kenney, Daniel Shen, Neelaksh Varshney, Samantha Sutton

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ECFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: enhanced cyan fluorescent protein derived from A. victoria GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Cyan fluorescent protein (ECFP) reporter coding sequence without the Ribosome Binding Site. Modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein and faster fall time for the emission.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_E0022 cyan fluorescent protein is based on BioBrick part BBa_E0021. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LVA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman
